      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i ran it through the scanner and it actually gave us a decent score but it's still sitting at like 65%. it's saying we're missing a lot of the granular regulatory terminology that the auditors look for in these HNW memos. \n\nbasically it's flagging that we haven't hit enough of the specific compliance markers. can you expand this? try to go much deeper into the legal specifics and make sure you're hitting every possible regulatory keyword or standard that would apply to anti-money laundering and identity verification. just make it really dense with the technical compliance language so we don't get a second rejection. thanks!!",
